---
description: "Branch discipline: never modify main/master; create feature branches before edits"
alwaysApply: true
---

Before ANY file modifications:
- Check current branch using: `git branch --show-current`
- If current branch is `main` or `master`:
  - Create and switch to a feature branch:
    - `feat/{task.id}-{slug}`
  - Record the branch name in `{artifact root}/plan.md`.

Hard stop:
- If you cannot create/switch branches, mark the task BLOCKED and do not edit files.